23... Rc2 24. Rxd4 Kg7 25. Nh5+ Kh7 26. Rf4 Rf8 27. Rb4
{ White has a solid advantage. The White Knight will usually reroute to Ne4 or Nd6. The White King often slowly improves itself to g3. White should usually not trade Rooks in order to hold the queenside pawns. Eventually, the passed kingside pawns should become a winning threat. }
