1. Bg5 Qxg5 2. Bxd7+ Kxd7 3. Qxe6+ Kd8 4. Qxd5+ Ke8
{ 18...Kc8  19.Qe6+  Kb8  20.Qe5+  Kc8  21.Ne6  threatening mate  21...Qe7  O-O-O  with victory in sight. }
5. Qb5+
{ Black has no defense. They can never step to d8 due to Ne6+ winning the Queen.   19...Ke7  is mate in 8 after  20.Qxb7+  Kf6  21.Ne4+  Ke5  22.Qc7+  Kxe4  23.Qc6+  Ke5  24.Qe6+  Kxd4  25.c3+  Kc5  26.b4+  Kb5  27.a4#  . This alternative  19...Kf7  is no better after  20.Nxf5  with too many discovery threats  20...Bxf5  21.Rxf5+  will pick up the Queen. }
*

