1. Qf2 Nxg4 2. Qe2
{ White ends up with a winning position regardless of how Black responds.   2...Ne3  3.Bxe3  dxe3  4.Qxe3  and threats of  Nxd5  and having the piece for 3 pawns give White a winning position against the exposed Black King.  The natural   2...Nf6  loses to  3.Nxe6  fxe6  4.Qxe6+  Be7  Blocking with  Qe7  is no better after  Nc7+  followed by a trade of Queens and capture of the Rook  5.Bf4  when  Nd6+  is decisive. }
*

